{
  "id": 132739,
  "referenceId": 108793,
  "name": "John 8:31–59",
  "localizedName": "John 8:31–59",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus said that those who obey him understand the truth about who he is. This truth sets people free."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The religious leaders argued that they were already free. They were sure of their own "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108220",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "family line"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and that they weren’t "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108258",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "slaves"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". But Jesus explained that they were slaves to sin. Sin kept them from being fully part of God’s family."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus could set them free from their sin and make them part of God’s family. He could do this because he is the Son in God’s family."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The leaders claimed they were already in God’s family because Abraham was their father. They said that God was their Father too. But Jesus said that they didn’t act like Abraham or do what God wanted. When Abraham heard from God, he believed God and obeyed God’s words. But the religious leaders refused to believe God’s words through Jesus and didn’t obey him."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "By not obeying the truth, they were acting like the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108216",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "devil"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Jesus said that those who obey him would never die. He was talking about when God will raise them from the dead. That is when God will give them eternal life."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus spoke about himself as "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108304",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "I am"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". This was a way for Jesus to tell people that he is God. This made the Jewish leaders so angry that they tried to kill him."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
